That which is affixed; an appendage.
A bound morpheme added to the word’s stem's end.
(broadly) A bound morpheme added to a word’s stem; a prefix, suffix etc.
The complex number a+bi associated with the point in the Gauss plane with coordinates (a,b).
(decorative art) Any small feature, as a figure, a flower, or the like, added for ornament to a vessel or other utensil, to an architectural feature.
To attach.
definitions.example: to affix a stigma to a person

definitions.definition: To subjoin, annex, or add at the close or end; to append to.
definitions.example: to affix a seal to an instrument

definitions.definition: To fix or fasten figuratively; with on or upon.
definitions.example: eyes affixed upon the ground

definitions.definition: To have or express as an opinion; to opine.
To have a given opinion.
Having very strong opinions.
Holding to one's own opinion obstinately and unreasonably.
An idiosyncrasy; a slight glitch, mannerism; something unusual about the manner or style of something or someone
definitions.example: The car steers cleanly, but the gearshift has a few quirks.

definitions.definition: An acute angle dividing a molding; a groove that runs lengthwise between the upper part of a moulding and a soffit
A quibble, evasion, or subterfuge.
To move with a wry jerk.
definitions.example: He quirked an eyebrow.

definitions.definition: To furnish with a quirk or channel.
To use verbal tricks or quibbles
To administer the vows of a religious order to (someone); to admit to a religious order. (Chiefly in passive.)
To declare oneself (to be something).
To declare; to assert, affirm.
To make a claim (to be something); to lay claim to (a given quality, feeling etc.), often with connotations of insincerity.
To declare one's adherence to (a religion, deity, principle etc.).
To work as a professor of; to teach.
To claim to have knowledge or understanding of (a given area of interest, subject matter).
Openly declared or acknowledged.
definitions.example: His professed religion was Catholicism.

definitions.definition: Professing to be qualified.
definitions.example: She is a professed expert in mechanics.

definitions.definition: Having no rival; better than any possible competitor
